

BenQ Mobile has agreed to become the main sponsor of Spanish football club Real Madrid, the team's official website said on Tuesday.

Jose Angel Sanchez, head of marketing at Real said the club was "very happy with its new main sponsor": a joint venture between Chinese Taipei-based BenQ Corporation and German technology firm Siemens AG.

Clemence Joos, president of BenQ said that Real Madrid's most important and attractive features were its professionalism, quality and teamwork.

